TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
Format the information needed to build parameter rows.
ITPR009414 - Added 3 new rows to output parm file for Aetna workflow.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Format_Parameters

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This port was added as part of the ITPR009414 Aetna project. Aetna needed a supplemental PBA lookup occur after they locked the period, so we added it to the process controller steps to run when models were closed. However, we don't want our workflow to run and try to populate Aetna claims when GPO is being locked. This added section in the parameter file used for the closed period workflows will enable us to check the MODEL that is being processed, and not execute our sessions when it is not model type T.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: -- Folder, Workflow and Workflow Name - NO SESSION, this is a WF parameter file '[Rebates_Aetna.WF:wf_m_BCA_BCI_CDD_max_lock_prd]'
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: wf_m_BCA_BCI_CDD_max_lock_prd_Closed_Period_Header1

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This variable setting must be part of the section for the wf_m_BCA_BCI_CDD_max_lock_prd to allow the Get Period Dates session to read not only the workflow parameter file, but the session parameter file. Without this option, the session parameter file is not used at all in the session, due to the presence of the workflow parameter file.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Allow_WF_and_Session_Parm_Files

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF( NOT ISNULL(MODEL_TYP_CD) ,'$$MODEL_TYP_CD=' || MODEL_TYP_CD ,ABORT('Model Type parameter not supplied to process.') )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Parm_MODEL_TYP_CD

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF( NOT ISNULL(INV_ELIG_DT) ,'$$INV_ELIG_DT=' || INV_ELIG_DT ,ABORT('Invoice Eligibility Date parameter not supplied to process.') )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Parm_INV_ELIG_DT

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF( NOT ISNULL(PRD_ID) ,'$$PRD_ID=' || PRD_ID ,ABORT('Period ID parameter not supplied to process.') )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Parm_PRD_ID

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: DECODE(:LKP.LKP_CLOSED_PERIOD (MODEL_TYP_CD, INV_ELIG_DT_lkp, PRD_ID_lkp) ,NULL, ABORT('Parameters are NOT a valid period.') ,'L', '$$MODEL_TYP_DESC=' || :LKP.LKP_MODEL_TYPE_DESC (MODEL_TYP_CD) ,ABORT('Model/Period is NOT closed.') )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: Parm_MODEL_TYP_DESC

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Used to confirm whether a period is Closed.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_Closed_Period

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: MODEL_TYP_CD = MODEL_TYP_CD_in AND MNTH_PERIOD_END_DT = INV_ELIG_DT_in AND PRD_ID = PRD_ID_in

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This SQL pulls data from RCIT_PRCS_CNTL, RCIT_PRCS_CNTL_DTL and RCIT_PRCS_OVRD_RULE. The Overrides Rule rows [currently 3] contain the Model, Invoice Eligibility Date and Period of the period that was closed. Those values were created by the RCI Manager, selected by Business.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_RCIT_PRCS_CNTL

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: User Defined Join
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: -- join condition vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL.PRCS_GID = vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL_DTL.PRCS_GID AND vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL_DTL.PRCS_GID = vrap.RCIT_PRCS_OVRD_RULE.PRCS_GID

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Source Filter
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
-- filter condition
vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL.PRCS_STAT_CD = 2 AND vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL_DTL.PRCS_DTL_STAT_CD = 2 AND vrap.RCIT_PRCS_CNTL.PRCS_APPL_ID = 'RCI'
-- PRCS_STAT_CD = 2 indicates currently Main running -- PRCS_DTL_STAT_CD = 2 indicates currently running Detail process

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Aggregate the Override Rule values [in RCIT_PRCS_OVRD_RULE] into one for for the PRCS_GID. Currently, there are three values; Model, Invoice Eligibility Date and Period
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: AGG_Ovrd_Rules

TASK.DESCRIPTION: Send e-mail stating an active process was not found.
TASK.NAME: Email_Cannot_Find_Process

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Subject
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: FAILURE: Refreshing Closed Period Reporting Parameters

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
ONCALL: This occurs when the mapping cannot find a Process Controller process with a main and detail process in 2=RUNNING status. Use the RCI Mananger or query RCIT_PRCS_CNTL [PRCS_STAT_CD=2] and RCIT_PRCS_CNTL_DTL [PRCS_DTL_STAT_CD=2] to find one. If one cannot be found, then this process should not have run.
Additionally, this could occur if no parameters [Model, Invoice Eligilibity Date and Period] were not supplied. Table RCIT_PRCS_OVRD_RULE should contain 3 rows [one for each parameter], associated with a running PRCS_GID.
IF the process should have run, after determining and fixing the cause of the error, please ReStart THIS STEP.
--------------------------------------------------
The mapping m_Refresh_Balance_Parameters_Closed_Period ran in the s_m_Refresh_Balance_Parameters_Closed_Period session in the wf_m_Refresh_Balance_Parameters_Closed_Period workflow.

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: NO Overrides This process expects to find a Main and Detail running process. If one is not found [TargetSuccess=0], then the next process [e-mail] is run.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_Refresh_Balance_Parameters_Closed_Period

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: Send e-mail stating an active process was not found.
